# .cursorrules — Agent Entry for Cursor

**Last updated:** 2026-05-12

---

## Project: Affiliate Intelligence (Programmatic SEO Content Machine)

Automated content publishing system: AI-generated articles → Next.js website → AdSense + affiliate monetisation → video pipeline (Phase 4).

---

## Read These First

1. `.ai-context/project.md` — Project overview
2. `.ai-context/conventions.md` — Coding style & naming rules
3. `.ai-context/architecture.md` — System diagram & data flow
4. `.ai-context/data-schema.md` — Database schema (keywords table)

## Authoritative Specs

- `docs/SPEC-01-content-bot.md` — Python content pipeline
- `docs/SPEC-02-web-system.md` — Next.js website
- `docs/SPEC-03-monetisation.md` — AdSense + affiliate
- `docs/SPEC-04-video-pipeline.md` — Video pipeline (Phase 4)

SPEC files override any other documentation when conflicts exist.

---

## Rules

- Python → `apps/bot/`, `black` + `ruff`, type hints required
- TypeScript/React → `apps/web/`, Prettier + ESLint, strict mode
- Never commit `.env` or API keys
- No code comments unless asked
- Commits: `type(scope): description` (e.g. `feat(s01): add keyword selector`)
- Lint before commit: `ruff check apps/bot/` + `npx eslint apps/web/`
- Test before commit: `pytest apps/bot/tests/` + `npm run test --prefix apps/web/`

---

## Data Flow

```
keywords.db → SPEC-01 Bot → MDX files → SPEC-02 Next.js → Vercel → Public Site
                                                              ↓
                                                   AdSense + Affiliate (SPEC-03)
                                                              ↓
                                                   GSC Feedback → keywords.db
```

---

## Schema Change Protocol

1. Update `.ai-context/data-schema.md`
2. Update relevant SPEC file
3. Write migration script in `data/migrations/`
4. Implement code changes
5. Update `architecture.md` if flow changed
